files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.AttentiveNAS<T>
files.Summary:
AttentiveNAS: Improving Neural Architecture Search via Attentive Sampling. Uses an attention-based meta-network to guide the sampling of sub-networks, focusing search on promising regions of the architecture space.

Reference: "AttentiveNAS: Improving Neural Architecture Search via Attentive Sampling" (CVPR 2021)

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.AttentiveNASConfig<T>
files.Summary: Configuration for an AttentiveNAS sub-network.

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.BigNAS<T>
files.Summary:
BigNAS: Scaling Up Neural Architecture Search with Big Single-Stage Models. Combines sandwich sampling with in-place knowledge distillation to train very large super-networks that can adapt to various deployment scenarios.

Reference: "BigNAS: Scaling Up Neural Architecture Search with Big Single-Stage Models"

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.BigNASConfig
files.Summary: Configuration for a BigNAS sub-network.

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.ENAS<T>
files.Summary:
Efficient Neural Architecture Search via Parameter Sharing. ENAS uses a controller RNN to sample architectures and shares weights among child models, achieving 1000x speedup over standard NAS.

Reference: "Efficient Neural Architecture Search via Parameter Sharing" (ICML 2018)

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.FBNet<T>
files.Summary:
FBNet: Hardware-Aware Efficient ConvNet Design via Differentiable Neural Architecture Search. Uses Gumbel-Softmax with hardware latency constraints to find efficient architectures optimized for specific target devices.

Reference: "FBNet: Hardware-Aware Efficient ConvNet Design via Differentiable NAS" (CVPR 2019)

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.GDAS<T>
files.Summary:
Gradient-based Differentiable Architecture Search with Gumbel-Softmax sampling. GDAS uses Gumbel-Softmax to make the architecture search fully differentiable while maintaining discrete selection during forward pass.

Reference: "Searching for A Robust Neural Architecture in Four GPU Hours" (CVPR 2019)

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.OnceForAll<T>
files.Summary:
Once-for-All (OFA) Networks: Train Once, Specialize for Anything. Trains a single large network that supports diverse architectural configurations, enabling instant specialization to different hardware platforms without retraining.

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.PCDARTS<T>
files.Summary:
Partial Channel Connections for Memory-Efficient Differentiable Architecture Search. PC-DARTS reduces memory consumption by sampling only a subset of channels during the search, making it more scalable to larger search spaces and datasets.

Reference: "PC-DARTS: Partial Channel Connections for Memory-Efficient Architecture Search" (ICLR 2020)

files.Title: AiDotNet.AutoML.NAS.ProxylessNAS<T>
files.Summary:
ProxylessNAS: Direct Neural Architecture Search on Target Task and Hardware. Uses path binarization and latency-aware loss to search directly on the target device without requiring a proxy task or separate hardware lookup tables.

Reference: "ProxylessNAS: Direct Neural Architecture Search on Target Task and Hardware" (ICLR 2019)

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.AlgebraicSimplificationPass<T>
files.Summary:
Applies algebraic simplification rules to reduce computational complexity. Examples:

  • x * 1 = x
  • x + 0 = x
  • x * 0 = 0
  • x / 1 = x
  • x^1 = x
  • x^0 = 1

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.CommonSubexpressionEliminationPass<T>
files.Summary: Eliminates common subexpressions by sharing computation. If the same operation with the same inputs appears multiple times, compute it once and reuse the result.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.ConstantFoldingPass<T>
files.Summary: Folds constant expressions at compile time to reduce runtime computation. For example: If two constants are multiplied, compute the result once during optimization rather than every inference call.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.ConvBatchNormFusionPass<T>
files.Summary: Fuses Convolution + BatchNormalization into a single operation. This is a critical optimization that eliminates the normalization overhead during inference.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.ConvBatchNormReLUFusionPass<T>
files.Summary: Fuses Convolution + BatchNormalization + ReLU into a single operation. This is one of the most common patterns in CNNs (ResNet, VGG, etc.) and provides significant speedup by reducing memory traffic and kernel launches.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.DeadCodeEliminationPass<T>
files.Summary: Eliminates nodes that don't contribute to the output (dead code). This includes nodes with no consumers and nodes that are not reachable from outputs.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.ElementwiseFusionPass<T>
files.Summary: Fuses consecutive elementwise operations into a single operation. For example: (x + y) * z can be computed in a single fused kernel. This reduces memory bandwidth by avoiding intermediate results.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.IOptimizationPass<T>
files.Summary: Interface for optimization passes that transform computation graphs to improve inference performance.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.InPlaceOptimizationPass<T>
files.Summary: Marks operations that can be performed in-place to reduce memory allocation. Operations like ReLU, Dropout, and some elementwise operations can modify their input tensors directly instead of allocating new memory.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.LayoutOptimizationPass<T>
files.Summary:
Optimizes tensor layout (NCHW vs NHWC) for better hardware utilization. Different hardware architectures prefer different layouts:

  • NCHW: Better for GPUs (NVIDIA)
  • NHWC: Better for some CPUs and TPUs

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.MatMulBiasActivationFusionPass<T>
files.Summary: Fuses MatMul + Bias + Activation (ReLU, GELU, etc.) into a single operation. This is the most common pattern in transformer feed-forward networks and MLPs.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.MatMulBiasFusionPass<T>
files.Summary: Fuses MatMul + Bias (Add) operations into a single Gemm operation. This is extremely common in fully connected layers and transformers.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.MemoryReuseOptimizationPass<T>
files.Summary: Optimizes memory usage by reusing buffers for different operations. Analyzes the lifetime of tensors and assigns memory pools to reduce overall memory footprint during inference.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.MultiHeadAttentionFusionPass<T>
files.Summary: Fuses multi-head attention components into a single optimized operation. Multi-head attention consists of multiple Q, K, V projections, attention computation, and output projection. Fusing these provides significant speedup in transformers.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.OptimizationPassBase<T>
files.Summary: Base class for optimization passes.

files.Title: AiDotNet.InferenceOptimization.Passes.StrengthReductionPass<T>
files.Summary:
Replaces expensive operations with cheaper equivalent operations. Examples:

  • x^2 -> x * x
  • x * 2 -> x + x
  • x / 2 -> x * 0.5
  • sqrt(x^2) -> abs(x)

files.Title: AiDotNet.Metrics.FrechetInceptionDistance<T>
files.Summary:
Frchet Inception Distance (FID) - A metric for evaluating the quality of generated images.

FID measures how similar generated images are to real images by comparing their statistical properties in a feature space. Lower FID scores indicate better quality.

The algorithm:

  1. Extract features from images using a pre-trained neural network
  2. Compute statistics (mean and covariance) for real and generated image features
  3. Compute the Frchet distance between the two Gaussian distributions

Formula: FID = || - || + Tr( + - 2()) where is mean, is covariance, Tr is trace

Typical FID scores:

  • FID less than 10: Excellent quality
  • FID 10-20: Good quality
  • FID 20-50: Moderate quality
  • FID greater than 50: Poor quality

Based on "GANs Trained by a Two Time-Scale Update Rule Converge to a Local Nash Equilibrium" by Heusel et al. (2017)

files.Title: AiDotNet.NeuralNetworks.BigGAN<T>
files.Summary:
BigGAN implementation for large-scale high-fidelity image generation.

For Beginners: BigGAN is a state-of-the-art GAN architecture that generates extremely high-quality images by scaling up training in several ways:

  1. Using very large batch sizes (256-2048 images at once)
  2. Increasing model capacity (more parameters and feature maps)
  3. Using class information to generate specific types of images

Think of it like training an artist:

  • Small batch = showing the artist 1-2 examples at a time
  • BigGAN batch = showing 256+ examples at once for better learning
  • Class conditioning = telling the artist exactly what to draw ("draw a cat" vs "draw something")

Key innovations:

  1. Large Batch Training: Uses batch sizes of 256-2048 (vs typical 32-128)
  2. Spectral Normalization: Stabilizes training for both G and D
  3. Self-Attention: Helps model long-range dependencies in images
  4. Class Conditioning: Uses class embeddings for controlled generation
  5. Truncation Trick: Trade diversity for quality at generation time
  6. Orthogonal Initialization: Better weight initialization
  7. Skip Connections: Direct paths in generator architecture

Based on "Large Scale GAN Training for High Fidelity Natural Image Synthesis" by Brock et al. (2019)

files.Title: AiDotNet.NeuralNetworks.Layers.ActivationLayer<T>
files.Summary:
A layer that applies an activation function to transform the input data.

Activation functions introduce non-linearity to neural networks. Non-linearity means the output isn't simply proportional to the input (like y = 2x). Instead, it can follow curves or more complex patterns. severely limiting what it can learn.

Common activation functions include: - ReLU: Returns 0 for negative inputs, or the input value for positive inputs - Sigmoid: Squashes values between 0 and 1, useful for probabilities - Tanh: Similar to sigmoid but outputs values between -1 and 1

files.Title: AiDotNet.NeuralNetworks.ProgressiveGAN<T>
files.Summary:
Production-ready Progressive GAN (ProGAN) implementation that generates high-resolution images by progressively growing the generator and discriminator during training.

For Beginners: Progressive GAN is a technique for training GANs that can generate very high-resolution images (e.g., 1024x1024 pixels). Instead of trying to generate high-resolution images from the start, it begins by generating small images (e.g., 4x4) and progressively adds new layers to both the generator and discriminator to increase the resolution (4x4 8x8 16x16 32x32 64x64 128x128 256x256 1024x1024).

Key innovations:

  1. Progressive Growing: Start with low resolution and gradually add layers
  2. Smooth Fade-in: New layers are faded in smoothly using a blending parameter (alpha)
  3. Minibatch Standard Deviation: Helps prevent mode collapse by adding diversity
  4. Equalized Learning Rate: Normalizes weights at runtime for better training dynamics
  5. Pixel Normalization: Normalizes feature vectors in generator to prevent escalation

Based on "Progressive Growing of GANs for Improved Quality, Stability, and Variation" by Karras et al. (2018)

files.Title: AiDotNet.NeuralNetworks.SAGAN<T>
files.Summary:
Self-Attention GAN (SAGAN) implementation that uses self-attention mechanisms to model long-range dependencies in generated images.

For Beginners: Traditional CNNs in GANs only look at nearby pixels (local receptive fields). This works well for textures and local patterns, but struggles with global structure and long-range relationships (like making sure both eyes of a face look similar, or ensuring consistent geometric patterns).

Self-Attention solves this by letting each pixel "attend to" all other pixels, similar to how Transformers work in NLP. Think of it as:

  • CNN: "I can only see my immediate neighbors"
  • Self-Attention: "I can see the entire image and decide what's important"

Example: When generating a dog's face:

  • CNN: Might make one ear pointy and one floppy (inconsistent)
  • SAGAN: Notices both ears and makes them match (consistent)

Key innovations:

  1. Self-Attention Layers: Allow modeling of long-range dependencies
  2. Spectral Normalization: Stabilizes training for both G and D
  3. Hinge Loss: More stable than standard GAN loss
  4. Two Time-Scale Update Rule (TTUR): Different learning rates for G and D
  5. Conditional Batch Normalization: For class-conditional generation

Based on "Self-Attention Generative Adversarial Networks" by Zhang et al. (2019)

files.Title: AiDotNet.Optimizers.ModifiedGradientDescentOptimizer<T>
files.Summary:
Modified Gradient Descent optimizer for Hope architecture. Based on Equations 27-29 from "Nested Learning" paper.

Traditional GD: W_{t+1} = W_t - * L(W_t; x_t) x_t Modified GD: W_{t+1} = W_t * (I - x_t*x_t^T) - * L(W_t; x_t) x_t

This formulation uses L2 regression objective instead of dot-product similarity, resulting in better handling of data dependencies in token space.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Reasoning.Models.ThoughtNode<T>
files.Summary: Represents a node in a tree of thoughts, used for exploring multiple reasoning paths.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Reasoning.ReasoningMode
files.Summary: Available reasoning modes that determine how problems are solved.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Reasoning.ReasoningStrategyBase<T>
files.Summary: Abstract base class for reasoning strategies that solve problems through structured thinking. Provides common functionality for all reasoning approaches.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Reasoning.Strategies.ChainOfThoughtStrategy<T>
files.Summary: Implements Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning that solves problems through explicit step-by-step thinking.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Reasoning.Strategies.SearchAlgorithmType
files.Summary: Types of search algorithms available for Tree-of-Thoughts.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Reasoning.Strategies.SelfConsistencyStrategy<T>
files.Summary: Implements Self-Consistency reasoning by sampling multiple reasoning paths and using majority voting.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Reasoning.Strategies.TreeOfThoughtsStrategy<T>
files.Summary: Implements Tree-of-Thoughts (ToT) reasoning that explores multiple reasoning paths in a tree structure.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.AdaBoostR2Regression<T>
files.Summary: Implements the AdaBoost.R2 algorithm for regression problems, an ensemble learning method that combines multiple decision tree regressors to improve prediction accuracy.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.AsyncDecisionTreeRegressionBase<T>
files.Summary: Represents an abstract base class for asynchronous decision tree regression models.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.BayesianRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Bayesian Linear Regression with support for various kernels and uncertainty estimation.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.ConditionalInferenceTreeRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a conditional inference tree regression model that builds decision trees based on statistical tests.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.DecisionTreeRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a decision tree regression model that predicts continuous values based on input features.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.DecisionTreeRegressionBase<T>
files.Summary: Provides a base implementation for decision tree regression models that predict continuous values.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.ElasticNetRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Elastic Net Regression (combined L1 and L2 regularized linear regression), which extends ordinary least squares by adding both L1 (Lasso) and L2 (Ridge) penalty terms.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.ExtremelyRandomizedTreesRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements an Extremely Randomized Trees regression model, which is an ensemble method that uses multiple decision trees with additional randomization for improved prediction accuracy and reduced overfitting.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.GaussianProcessRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements a Gaussian Process Regression model, which is a non-parametric, probabilistic approach to regression that provides uncertainty estimates along with predictions.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.GeneralizedAdditiveModel<T>
files.Summary: Implements a Generalized Additive Model (GAM) for regression, which models the target as a sum of smooth functions of individual features, allowing for flexible nonlinear relationships while maintaining interpretability.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.GeneticAlgorithmRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements a regression model that uses genetic algorithms to optimize model parameters, mimicking the process of natural selection to find the best solution.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.GradientBoostingRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements a Gradient Boosting Regression model, which combines multiple decision trees sequentially to create a powerful ensemble that learns from the errors of previous trees.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.IsotonicRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements an Isotonic Regression model, which fits a free-form line to data with the constraint that the fitted line must be non-decreasing (monotonically increasing).

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.KNearestNeighborsRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements K-Nearest Neighbors algorithm for regression, which predicts target values by averaging the values of the K closest training examples.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.KernelRidgeRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Kernel Ridge Regression, a powerful nonlinear regression technique that combines ridge regression with the kernel trick to capture complex nonlinear relationships.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.LassoRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Lasso Regression (L1 regularized linear regression), which extends ordinary least squares by adding a penalty term proportional to the absolute magnitude of the coefficients.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.LocallyWeightedRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Locally Weighted Regression, a non-parametric approach that creates a different model for each prediction point based on the weighted influence of nearby training examples.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.LogisticRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a logistic regression model for binary classification problems.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.M5ModelTree<T>
files.Summary: Represents an M5 model tree for regression problems, combining decision tree structure with linear models at the leaves.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.MultilayerPerceptronRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a multilayer perceptron (neural network) for regression problems.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.MultinomialLogisticRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a multinomial logistic regression model for multi-class classification problems.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.MultipleRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a multiple linear regression model that predicts a target value based on multiple input features.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.MultivariateRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a multivariate linear regression model that predicts a target value based on multiple input features.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.NegativeBinomialRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a negative binomial regression model for count data that may exhibit overdispersion.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.NeuralNetworkRegression<T>
files.Summary: A neural network regression model that can learn complex non-linear relationships in data.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.NonLinearRegressionBase<T>
files.Summary: Base class for non-linear regression algorithms that provides common functionality for training and prediction.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.OrthogonalRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements orthogonal regression (also known as total least squares), which minimizes the perpendicular distance from data points to the fitted line or hyperplane.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.PartialLeastSquaresRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Partial Least Squares Regression (PLS), a technique that combines features from principal component analysis and multiple linear regression to handle situations with many correlated predictors.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.PoissonRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Poisson regression, a generalized linear model used for modeling count data and contingency tables.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.PolynomialRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements polynomial regression, which extends linear regression by fitting a polynomial equation to the data.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.PrincipalComponentRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Principal Component Regression (PCR), a technique that combines principal component analysis (PCA) with linear regression to handle multicollinearity in the predictor variables.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.QuantileRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Quantile Regression, a technique that estimates the conditional quantiles of a response variable distribution in the linear model, providing a more complete view of the relationship between variables.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.QuantileRegressionForests<T>
files.Summary: Implements Quantile Regression Forests, an extension of Random Forests that can predict conditional quantiles of the target variable, not just the conditional mean.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.RadialBasisFunctionRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Radial Basis Function (RBF) Regression, a technique that uses radial basis functions as the basis for approximating complex nonlinear relationships between inputs and outputs.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.RandomForestRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Random Forest Regression, an ensemble learning method that operates by constructing multiple decision trees during training and outputting the average prediction of the individual trees.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.RegressionBase<T>
files.Summary: Provides a base implementation for regression algorithms that model the relationship between a dependent variable and one or more independent variables.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.RidgeRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Ridge Regression (L2 regularized linear regression), which extends ordinary least squares by adding a penalty term proportional to the squared magnitude of the coefficients.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.RobustRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a robust regression model that is resistant to outliers in the data.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.SimpleRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements simple linear regression, which predicts a single output value based on a single input feature. This is the most basic form of regression that finds the best-fitting straight line through a set of points.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.SplineRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements spline regression, which models nonlinear relationships by fitting piecewise polynomial functions. This advanced regression technique offers more flexibility than simple linear regression by allowing the model to change its behavior across different regions of the data.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.StepwiseRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements stepwise regression, which automatically selects the most relevant features for the model. This approach builds a model by adding or removing features based on their statistical significance.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.SupportVectorRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements Support Vector Regression (SVR), which creates a regression model by finding a hyperplane that lies within a specified margin (epsilon) of the training data. This approach is effective for both linear and nonlinear regression problems.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.SymbolicRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements symbolic regression, which discovers mathematical expressions that best describe the relationship between input features and target values. Unlike traditional regression methods, symbolic regression can discover both the form of the equation and its parameters.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.TimeSeriesRegression<T>
files.Summary: Represents a time series regression model that incorporates temporal dependencies, trends, and seasonality.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regression.WeightedRegression<T>
files.Summary: Implements weighted regression, a variation of linear regression where each data point has a different level of importance (weight) in determining the model parameters.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regularization.ElasticNetRegularization<T, TInput, TOutput>
files.Summary: Implements Elastic Net regularization, a hybrid approach that combines L1 (Lasso) and L2 (Ridge) regularization techniques.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regularization.L1Regularization<T, TInput, TOutput>
files.Summary: Implements L1 regularization (also known as Lasso), a technique that adds a penalty equal to the absolute value of the magnitude of coefficients.

files.Title: AiDotNet.Regularization.L2Regularization<T, TInput, TOutput>
files.Summary: Implements L2 regularization (also known as Ridge), a technique that adds a penalty equal to the square of the magnitude of coefficients.

files.Summary: Worker-local networks for A3C agent. Each worker maintains its own copy of policy and value networks.

files.Summary: LSPI (Least-Squares Policy Iteration) agent using iterative policy improvement with LSTDQ.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.AdvancedRL.LSTDAgent<T>
files.Summary: LSTD (Least-Squares Temporal Difference) agent using direct solution for value function weights.

files.Summary: Linear Q-Learning agent using linear function approximation.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.AdvancedRL.LinearSARSAAgent<T>
files.Summary: Linear SARSA agent using linear function approximation with on-policy learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.AdvancedRL.TabularActorCriticAgent<T>
files.Summary: Tabular Actor-Critic agent combining policy and value learning.

files.Summary: Epsilon-Greedy Multi-Armed Bandit agent.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.Bandits.GradientBanditAgent<T>
files.Summary: Gradient Bandit agent using softmax action preferences.

files.Summary: Thompson Sampling (Bayesian) Multi-Armed Bandit agent.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.Bandits.UCBBanditAgent<T>
files.Summary: Upper Confidence Bound (UCB) Multi-Armed Bandit agent.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.CQL.CQLAgent<T>
files.Summary: Conservative Q-Learning (CQL) agent for offline reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.DDPG.DDPGAgent<T>
files.Summary: Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) agent for continuous control.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.DQN.DQNAgent<T>
files.Summary: Deep Q-Network (DQN) agent for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.DecisionTransformer.DecisionTransformerAgent<T>
files.Summary: Decision Transformer agent for offline reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.DecisionTransformer.SequenceContext<T>
files.Summary: Context window for sequence modeling in Decision Transformer. Maintains recent states, actions, and returns-to-go for transformer input.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.DeepReinforcementLearningAgentBase<T>
files.Summary: Base class for deep reinforcement learning agents that use neural networks as function approximators.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.DoubleDQN.DoubleDQNAgent<T>
files.Summary: Double Deep Q-Network (Double DQN) agent for reinforcement learning.

files.Summary: Double Q-Learning agent using two Q-tables to reduce overestimation bias.

files.Summary: Dreamer agent for model-based reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.DuelingDQN.DuelingDQNAgent<T>
files.Summary: Dueling Deep Q-Network agent for reinforcement learning.

files.Summary: Modified Policy Iteration agent - hybrid of Policy Iteration and Value Iteration.

files.Summary: Policy Iteration agent for reinforcement learning using dynamic programming.

files.Summary: Helper class for serializing model transition data.

files.Summary: Value Iteration agent for reinforcement learning using dynamic programming.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.ExpectedSARSA.ExpectedSARSAAgent<T>
files.Summary: Expected SARSA agent using tabular methods.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.IQL.IQLAgent<T>
files.Summary: Implicit Q-Learning (IQL) agent for offline reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.MonteCarlo.EveryVisitMonteCarloAgent<T>
files.Summary: Every-Visit Monte Carlo agent that updates all visits to states in an episode.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.MonteCarlo.FirstVisitMonteCarloAgent<T>
files.Summary: First-Visit Monte Carlo agent for episodic tasks.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.MonteCarlo.MonteCarloExploringStartsAgent<T>
files.Summary: Monte Carlo Exploring Starts agent for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.MonteCarlo.OffPolicyMonteCarloAgent<T>
files.Summary: Off-Policy Monte Carlo Control agent with weighted importance sampling.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.MonteCarlo.OnPolicyMonteCarloAgent<T>
files.Summary: On-Policy Monte Carlo Control agent with epsilon-greedy exploration.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.MuZero.MCTSNode<T>
files.Summary: Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) node for MuZero agent. Represents a state in the search tree with visit counts and Q-values for actions.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.MuZero.MuZeroAgent<T>
files.Summary: MuZero agent combining tree search with learned models.

files.Summary: N-step Q-Learning agent using multi-step off-policy returns.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.PPO.PPOAgent<T>
files.Summary: Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) agent for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.Planning.DynaQAgent<T>
files.Summary: Dyna-Q agent combining learning and planning using a learned model.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.Planning.DynaQPlusAgent<T>
files.Summary: Dyna-Q+ agent with exploration bonus for handling changing environments.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.Planning.PrioritizedSweepingAgent<T>
files.Summary: Prioritized Sweeping agent that focuses planning on high-priority state-actions.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.QMIX.QMIXAgent<T>
files.Summary: QMIX agent for multi-agent value-based reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.REINFORCE.REINFORCEAgent<T>
files.Summary: REINFORCE (Monte Carlo Policy Gradient) agent for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.Rainbow.RainbowDQNAgent<T>
files.Summary: Rainbow DQN agent combining six extensions to DQN.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.ReinforcementLearningAgentBase<T>
files.Summary: Base class for all reinforcement learning agents, providing common functionality and structure.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.ReinforcementLearningOptions<T>
files.Summary: Configuration options for reinforcement learning agents.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.SAC.SACAgent<T>
files.Summary: Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) agent for continuous control reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.TD3.TD3Agent<T>
files.Summary: Twin Delayed Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (TD3) agent for continuous control.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.TRPO.TRPOAgent<T>
files.Summary: Trust Region Policy Optimization (TRPO) agent for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.TabularQLearning.TabularQLearningAgent<T>
files.Summary: Tabular Q-Learning agent using lookup table for Q-values.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Agents.WorldModels.WorldModelsAgent<T>
files.Summary: World Models agent learning compact representations with VAE and RNN.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Common.Trajectory<T>
files.Summary: Represents a trajectory of experience for on-policy RL algorithms (PPO, A2C, etc.).

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Environments.CartPoleEnvironment<T>
files.Summary: Classic CartPole-v1 environment for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Environments.DeterministicBanditEnvironment<T>
files.Summary: A deterministic multi-armed bandit environment for testing purposes.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.BetaPolicy<T>
files.Summary: Policy using Beta distribution for bounded continuous action spaces. Network outputs alpha and beta parameters for each action dimension. Actions are naturally bounded to [0, 1] and can be scaled to any [min, max] range.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.BetaPolicyOptions<T>
files.Summary: Configuration options for Beta distribution policies.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.ContinuousPolicy<T>
files.Summary: Policy for continuous action spaces using a neural network to output Gaussian parameters.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.ContinuousPolicyOptions<T>
files.Summary: Configuration options for continuous action space policies in reinforcement learning. Continuous policies output actions as real-valued vectors using Gaussian (normal) distributions.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.DeterministicPolicy<T>
files.Summary: Deterministic policy for continuous action spaces. Directly outputs actions without sampling from a distribution. Commonly used in DDPG, TD3, and other deterministic policy gradient methods.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.DeterministicPolicyOptions<T>
files.Summary: Configuration options for deterministic policies.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.DiscretePolicy<T>
files.Summary: Policy for discrete action spaces using a neural network to output action logits.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.DiscretePolicyOptions<T>
files.Summary: Configuration options for discrete action space policies in reinforcement learning. Discrete policies select from a finite set of actions using categorical (softmax) distributions.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.BoltzmannExploration<T>
files.Summary: Boltzmann (softmax) exploration with temperature-based action selection. Uses temperature parameter to control exploration: higher temperature = more random. Action probability: P(a) = exp(Q(a)/) / exp(Q(a')/)

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.EpsilonGreedyExploration<T>
files.Summary: Epsilon-greedy exploration: with probability epsilon, select random action.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.ExplorationStrategyBase<T>
files.Summary: Abstract base class for exploration strategy implementations. Provides common functionality for noise generation and action clamping.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.GaussianNoiseExploration<T>
files.Summary: Gaussian noise exploration for continuous action spaces.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.IExplorationStrategy<T>
files.Summary: Interface for exploration strategies used by policies.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.NoExploration<T>
files.Summary: No exploration - always use the policy's action directly (greedy).

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.OrnsteinUhlenbeckNoise<T>
files.Summary: Ornstein-Uhlenbeck process noise for temporally correlated exploration. Commonly used in DDPG and other continuous control algorithms. Process equation: dx = ( - x)dt + dW

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.ThompsonSamplingExploration<T>
files.Summary: Thompson Sampling (Bayesian) exploration for discrete action spaces. Maintains Beta distributions for each action and samples from posteriors.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.Exploration.UpperConfidenceBoundExploration<T>
files.Summary: Upper Confidence Bound (UCB) exploration for discrete action spaces. Balances exploration and exploitation using confidence intervals: UCB(a) = Q(a) + c * (ln(t) / N(a))

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.IPolicy<T>
files.Summary: Core interface for RL policies - defines how to select actions.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.MixedPolicy<T>
files.Summary: Policy for environments with both discrete and continuous action spaces. Outputs both categorical distribution for discrete actions and Gaussian for continuous actions. Common in robotics where you have discrete mode selection and continuous parameter control.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.MixedPolicyOptions<T>
files.Summary: Configuration options for mixed discrete and continuous policies.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.MultiModalPolicy<T>
files.Summary: Multi-modal policy using mixture of Gaussians for complex action distributions.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.MultiModalPolicyOptions<T>
files.Summary: Configuration options for multi-modal mixture of Gaussians policies.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.Policies.PolicyBase<T>
files.Summary: Abstract base class for policy implementations. Provides common functionality for numeric operations, random number generation, and resource management.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.ReplayBuffers.Experience<T, TState, TAction>
files.Summary: Represents a single experience tuple (s, a, r, s', done) for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.ReplayBuffers.IReplayBuffer<T, TState, TAction>
files.Summary: Interface for experience replay buffers used in reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.ReplayBuffers.PrioritizedReplayBuffer<T>
files.Summary: Prioritized experience replay buffer for reinforcement learning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.ReinforcementLearning.ReplayBuffers.UniformReplayBuffer<T, TState, TAction>
files.Summary: A replay buffer that samples experiences uniformly at random.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.ChainOfThoughtRetriever<T>
files.Summary: Chain-of-Thought retriever that generates reasoning steps before retrieving documents.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.FLARERetriever<T>
files.Summary: FLARE (Forward-Looking Active REtrieval) pattern that actively decides when and what to retrieve during generation.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.GraphRAG<T>
files.Summary: Graph-based RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) that combines knowledge graph traversal with vector search for enhanced retrieval.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.MultiStepReasoningRetriever<T>.MultiStepReasoningResult
files.Summary: Result of multi-step reasoning retrieval.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.MultiStepReasoningRetriever<T>.ReasoningStepResult
files.Summary: Represents a single reasoning step in the multi-step process.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.MultiStepReasoningRetriever<T>
files.Summary: Multi-step reasoning retriever that breaks down complex queries into sequential steps.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.SelfCorrectingRetriever<T>
files.Summary: Self-correcting retriever that iteratively refines answers through critique, error detection, and targeted re-retrieval.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.ToolAugmentedReasoningRetriever<T>.ToolAugmentedResult
files.Summary: Result of tool-augmented reasoning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.ToolAugmentedReasoningRetriever<T>.ToolInvocation
files.Summary: Represents a tool invocation during reasoning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.ToolAugmentedReasoningRetriever<T>
files.Summary: Tool-augmented reasoning retriever that can use external tools during reasoning.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.TreeOfThoughtsRetriever<T>
files.Summary: Tree-of-Thoughts retriever that explores multiple reasoning paths in a tree structure.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.AdvancedPatterns.VerifiedReasoningRetriever<T>
files.Summary: Verified reasoning retriever that validates each reasoning step with critic models.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.AgenticChunker
files.Summary: Production-ready intelligent chunker that decides where to split text based on semantic boundaries.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.ChunkingStrategyBase
files.Summary: Provides a base implementation for text chunking strategies with common functionality.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.CodeAwareTextSplitter
files.Summary: Code-aware text splitter that respects code structure and syntax.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.FixedSizeChunkingStrategy
files.Summary: A simple fixed-size text chunking strategy that splits text at character boundaries.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.HeaderBasedTextSplitter
files.Summary: Splits structured documents based on header tags (H1, H2, H3, etc.).

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.MarkdownTextSplitter
files.Summary: Markdown-aware text splitter that respects markdown structure.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.MultiModalTextSplitter
files.Summary: Multi-modal splitter for documents containing both text and images.

files.Title: AiDotNet.RetrievalAugmentedGeneration.ChunkingStrategies.RecursiveCharacterChunkingStrategy

files.Title: AiDotNet.Serving.Services.RequestBatcher
files.Summary:
High-performance request batcher that collects multiple inference requests and processes them as a single batch to maximize throughput.

Enhanced features (Issue #410):

  • Dynamic batching with multiple strategies (Timeout, Size, Adaptive, Bucket)
  • Priority-based request scheduling with fair scheduling and backpressure handling
  • Padding strategies for variable-length sequences (Minimal, Bucket, Fixed)
  • Performance monitoring with latency percentile tracking (p50, p95, p99)
  • Adaptive batch sizing based on latency and throughput metrics

Reliability improvements:

  • Uses Channel-based queue and background Task for robust batch processing
  • Eliminates Timer-based scheduling which can be unreliable in CI environments
  • Uses SemaphoreSlim with WaitAsync for non-blocking synchronization

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.DOGWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Implements the Derivative of Gaussian (DOG) wavelet, which is based on the nth derivative of the Gaussian function and is useful for detecting changes in signals.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.DaubechiesWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Implements Daubechies wavelets, which are a family of orthogonal wavelets characterized by a maximal number of vanishing moments for a given support width.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.FejrKorovkinWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Fejr-Korovkin wavelet function implementation for signal processing and analysis.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.GaborWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Gabor wavelet function implementation for time-frequency analysis and signal processing.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.GaussianWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Gaussian wavelet function implementation for signal processing and analysis.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.HaarWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Haar wavelet function implementation for signal processing and analysis.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.MexicanHatWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Mexican Hat wavelet function implementation for signal processing and analysis.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.MeyerWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Meyer wavelet function implementation for frequency domain analysis and signal processing.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.MorletWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Morlet wavelet function implementation for time-frequency analysis and signal processing.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.PaulWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Paul wavelet function implementation for complex signal analysis and processing.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.ReverseBiorthogonalWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Reverse Biorthogonal wavelet function implementation for signal processing and analysis.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.ShannonWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Represents a Shannon wavelet function implementation for signal processing and frequency analysis.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.SymletWavelet<T>
files.Summary: Implements Symlet wavelets, which are nearly symmetric wavelets proposed by Daubechies as modifications to the Daubechies wavelets with increased symmetry.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WaveletFunctions.WaveletFunctionBase<T>
files.Summary: Base class for all wavelet function implementations providing common functionality.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.BartlettHannWindow<T>
files.Summary: Implements the Bartlett-Hann window function for signal processing applications.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.BartlettWindow<T>

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.BlackmanHarrisWindow<T>
files.Summary: Implements the Blackman-Harris window function for signal processing applications.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.BlackmanNuttallWindow<T>

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.BlackmanWindow<T>

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.BohmanWindow<T>

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.CosineWindow<T>

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.FlatTopWindow<T>
files.Summary: Implements the Flat Top window function for signal processing applications.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.GaussianWindow<T>
files.Summary: Implements the Gaussian window function for signal processing applications.

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.HammingWindow<T>

files.Title: AiDotNet.WindowFunctions.HanningWindow<T>

files.Title: System.ArrayPolyfill
files.Summary: Extension methods for Array to add missing methods from newer .NET versions. Available for all frameworks.
